WEBVTT

00:06.072 --> 00:09.473
<i>FRANKIE: It's a great American tradition
to believe anything's possible.</i>

00:09.676 --> 00:12.474
<i>I don't know if it's the game shows
we were raised on or what.</i>

00:12.679 --> 00:15.648
<i>But secretly, we think
we're just one spin of the wheel...</i>

00:15.849 --> 00:19.080
<i>...or one roll of the dice away
from being a big winner.</i>

00:19.319 --> 00:23.653
<i>That kind of crazy, delusional thinking
is practically bred into us.</i>

00:23.857 --> 00:27.725
I'm at the mall in front of Hot Dogs USA
and this woman comes and tells me...

00:27.927 --> 00:31.727
...that I have what it takes
to be a model.

00:31.931 --> 00:33.330
[SUE SHRIEKS]

00:33.500 --> 00:36.401
- Wanna take this or should I jump in?
- Axl.

00:36.603 --> 00:38.093
A model?

00:38.338 --> 00:41.307
That's great.

00:41.508 --> 00:42.736
I know.

00:42.909 --> 00:45.002
And she said
she or one of her associates...

00:45.178 --> 00:48.705
...could train me to be a model
and even get me glossy headshots...

00:48.882 --> 00:51.248
...all for $500.

00:53.520 --> 00:54.544
Okay, look.

00:54.721 --> 00:56.211
I know what you are thinking...

00:56.389 --> 00:59.722
...but I've seen pictures of supermodels
when they were my age...

00:59.893 --> 01:01.588
...and they are not that great.

01:02.595 --> 01:05.063
She said I have it.

01:05.265 --> 01:08.257
If by "it" you mean
no chance of ever in a million years...

01:08.435 --> 01:10.460
...even if everybody else were dead.

01:10.703 --> 01:11.761
- Mom.
- Mike.

01:11.971 --> 01:15.270
- Axl.
- Honey, you totally have it.

01:15.442 --> 01:18.639
But what we don't have
is that kind of money.

01:18.878 --> 01:22.541
- If I save enough babysitting, can I do it?
- Sure.

01:22.715 --> 01:26.116
<i>FRANKIE: At a buck-fifty an hour,
I figured that was a bet worth taking.</i>

01:26.352 --> 01:27.751
Yay!

01:28.221 --> 01:29.381
[FRANKIE, SUE & BRICK SCREAM]

01:29.556 --> 01:30.614
Dude, blackout.

01:30.857 --> 01:33.985
Okay, everybody relax.
Axl, get the flashlights.

01:36.663 --> 01:38.927
Well, the neighbors' lights are on.

01:39.099 --> 01:41.761
Frankie, we paid the electric bill,
didn't we?

01:44.370 --> 01:47.464
This is an outrage.
If you're gonna shut off the power...

01:47.640 --> 01:49.301
...do it at the top of the hour...

01:49.476 --> 01:52.673
<i>...before I'm already hooked
on Conveyor Belt of Love.</i>

01:55.281 --> 01:57.078
Hey, hey, don't let the cold air out.

01:57.283 --> 02:00.081
You have one grab
and you eat what you get.

02:01.821 --> 02:03.254
Peas? Oh, this sucks.

02:03.423 --> 02:04.981
Well, sorry and thank you for playing.

02:05.158 --> 02:07.956
<i>MAN [IN INDIAN ACCENT OVER PHONE]:
Orson Electric, Charlie speaking.</i>

02:08.127 --> 02:09.755
Oh, hi. Shh, I got them.

02:09.929 --> 02:12.659
<i>MAN: How may I assist you
with excellent customer service?</i>

02:12.832 --> 02:15.164
Uh, yes. Hi, Charlie.

02:15.702 --> 02:18.193
This is Frankie Heck
from 427 Birchwood.

02:18.404 --> 02:20.702
<i>- You shut off our power?
MAN: That is correct.</i>

02:20.907 --> 02:22.636
<i>You are three months behind
on payment.</i>

02:22.809 --> 02:24.140
FRANKIE:
That must be a mistake...

02:24.344 --> 02:27.279
...because I talked to Peggy
in the Orson office last week...

02:27.447 --> 02:29.005
...about a payment next Tuesday?

02:29.215 --> 02:30.682
<i>[MOUTHS]
Really?</i>

02:30.917 --> 02:35.149
And she was very nice. She promised me
that the power would stay on till then.

02:35.321 --> 02:36.447
Promised.

02:36.623 --> 02:38.352
<i>MAN:
I do not see that note in my system.</i>

02:38.525 --> 02:41.426
<i>Please hold for our automated
customer satisfaction survey.</i>

02:42.562 --> 02:45.963
Oh, well. I'll go down there tomorrow
and take care of it in person.

02:46.499 --> 02:48.160
Mike, cold air, cold air.

02:48.334 --> 02:49.562
Beer.

02:50.303 --> 02:51.497
I know the shape well.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.367
FRANKIE: How'd this happen?
I figured if we kept plugging holes...

02:54.541 --> 02:56.441
...till the quarry reopened,
we'd be okay.

02:56.643 --> 02:59.009
- Well, we figured wrong.
FRANKIE: Mm.

03:00.079 --> 03:01.239
MIKE:
When they laid me off...

03:01.447 --> 03:03.915
...they gave me the name
of that financial planner...

03:04.083 --> 03:06.142
...who will give a free consultation.

03:06.352 --> 03:08.217
We were too proud back then...

03:08.388 --> 03:12.381
...but when I look at it
in the, uh, harsh glow of candlelight...

03:12.559 --> 03:14.026
...tsk, maybe we should call.

03:14.194 --> 03:15.525
FRANKIE:
Mm-hm.

03:18.565 --> 03:19.862
Whipped cream!

03:21.234 --> 03:23.395
Okay, here's the thing.

03:23.570 --> 03:28.098
You can keep it or give it to Mom,
you get a free bonus grab.

03:28.341 --> 03:30.502
Bonus grab.

03:34.547 --> 03:36.276
Oh, sauerkraut.

03:36.516 --> 03:39.781
Good try, though. Good try.

03:40.019 --> 03:42.351
<i>FRANKIE: After a healthy breakfast
of olives and butter...</i>

03:42.522 --> 03:44.422
<i>...Brick was dealt another bad hand.</i>

03:44.591 --> 03:48.027
<i>See, Brick and a few kids
who were in his social-skills group...</i>

03:48.228 --> 03:51.925
<i>...liked to spend recess in the peace
and quiet of the library, until...</i>

03:52.098 --> 03:54.430
All right, boys,
I need you to come with me.

03:55.368 --> 03:57.632
We're instituting a new school policy.

03:58.137 --> 04:01.038
One you'll actually find lots of fun.

04:01.241 --> 04:02.572
Wait.

04:02.742 --> 04:04.073
This leads to the...

04:04.277 --> 04:05.904
[CHILDREN SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

04:06.079 --> 04:07.740
Playground.

04:07.947 --> 04:09.039
SEIFRIED:
That's right.

04:09.215 --> 04:12.241
From now on,
the library will be closed at recess...

04:12.418 --> 04:14.318
...and all students must play outside.

04:14.554 --> 04:16.317
Have fun.

04:16.522 --> 04:18.216
BOY 1:
Hey, wait. I got it.

04:18.423 --> 04:20.084
[BOY 2 YELLS THEN GRUNTS]

04:24.731 --> 04:26.392
[GIRLS SHRIEK]

04:26.599 --> 04:27.964
We can't stay here.

04:30.036 --> 04:33.665
Okay, if we can make it to that slide
over there, I think we'll be safe.

04:33.840 --> 04:34.932
Hoodies up.

04:35.441 --> 04:37.102
Follow me.

04:42.782 --> 04:44.841
HENRY:
Help!

04:46.586 --> 04:47.848
[HENRY WHIMPERING]

04:48.054 --> 04:50.454
We'll send help when we reach safety.

04:50.957 --> 04:52.652
[WHISPERS]
Safety.

04:56.362 --> 04:57.852
God. Where is this guy?

04:58.064 --> 05:00.658
He's been looking at our paperwork
for over 25 minutes.

05:00.833 --> 05:03.199
Five more minutes, he starts charging.

05:03.770 --> 05:06.671
- Hello, Mr. Heck.
- Cut to the chase, five minutes.

05:06.839 --> 05:08.773
How screwed are we
and what do we do?

05:08.975 --> 05:11.375
Well,
you're doing a lot of things right.

05:11.611 --> 05:12.635
MIKE:
Mm-hm, mm-hm.

05:12.812 --> 05:16.077
All right, long story short,
you're spending more than you earn.

05:16.282 --> 05:18.307
So we need to find places
you can cut back.

05:18.484 --> 05:20.714
So we're looking
for unnecessary expenses.

05:20.953 --> 05:23.387
Okay, okay.
Category is unnecessary expenses.

05:23.623 --> 05:26.387
Insurance, phone. Mike, help me.

05:26.959 --> 05:28.984
- Gas.
- Heat, cleaning products...

05:29.195 --> 05:30.355
- Gas.
- Said that already.

05:30.530 --> 05:32.020
- Orthodontist.
- Nice.

05:32.198 --> 05:34.826
Those are necessary expenses.
We're looking for extras.

05:35.001 --> 05:36.798
You know,
things you could do without.

05:37.170 --> 05:40.833
Oh, God, there are none.
We've already cut back on everything.

05:41.007 --> 05:43.237
Steve, come to our house.
Nothing good there.

05:43.476 --> 05:46.536
How about that $3 coffee?
How often do you get that?

05:46.746 --> 05:48.873
- Every day.
- Not very oft...

05:49.315 --> 05:50.805
Are you on my team here or not?

05:50.983 --> 05:53.178
Times five days a week
times 52 weeks a year.

05:53.353 --> 05:55.378
Hey, that's $750 right there.

05:55.621 --> 05:57.748
- Hoo.
- He buys imported beer.

05:57.924 --> 05:59.516
Imported from Ohio. Thanks, pal.

05:59.692 --> 06:00.886
You started it. Add that.

06:01.060 --> 06:03.187
Go ahead, add that, Steve.
Add the beer.

06:03.396 --> 06:06.661
She buys pop at the drive-thru
even though we have pop at home.

06:06.866 --> 06:09.232
Wait a minute. This is part of his plan.

06:09.435 --> 06:12.427
Turn us against each other
so we lose track of time.

06:13.539 --> 06:15.063
Yeah, that's my plan.

06:15.241 --> 06:18.335
Here's the thing.
Spend less, cut back, pay off your debts.

06:18.945 --> 06:21.436
Seven of your credit cards
have doubled their rates.

06:21.647 --> 06:22.875
Pay them down.

06:23.082 --> 06:24.913
Okay, wait a second.

06:25.084 --> 06:27.245
I have one really important question.
What if we...?

06:27.420 --> 06:28.444
[TIMER DINGS]

06:28.654 --> 06:30.281
Never mind.

06:38.631 --> 06:40.223
We're eating at the table?

06:40.433 --> 06:42.196
Oh, no. Dad's dying.

06:42.435 --> 06:43.459
Nobody's dying.

06:43.636 --> 06:46.730
We're just eating the stuff
out of the fridge before it goes bad.

06:46.939 --> 06:51.069
Dad grilled the crap out of everything
but I would still give it the sniff test.

06:51.244 --> 06:54.680
MIKE: Now listen, your mom and I
met with this financial advisor today.

06:54.881 --> 06:56.348
And he says we're doing good.

06:56.516 --> 06:58.882
We just gotta manage our money
a little better...

06:59.085 --> 07:02.350
...which means
that until the quarry reopens...

07:02.522 --> 07:04.490
...we just gotta find ways to cut back.

07:05.191 --> 07:07.352
I vote we let Brick go.
He's the weakest link.

07:07.527 --> 07:09.722
I say we leave him in the woods
and walk away.

07:09.962 --> 07:10.986
Great suggestion.

07:11.164 --> 07:14.531
But how about we buy less
takeout food and I cook more?

07:14.734 --> 07:16.531
I'll take my chances in the woods.

07:16.736 --> 07:18.601
Hey,
we gotta make tough choices here.

07:18.771 --> 07:21.103
I'm not saying it's gonna be easy.

07:21.274 --> 07:24.505
Like, I know that we love it...

07:24.710 --> 07:27.543
...but it's really expensive
and we really don't need it...

07:27.713 --> 07:29.772
...so we're getting rid of cable.

07:30.016 --> 07:32.712
SUE: No!
- Mom's cooking and no TV?

07:32.885 --> 07:34.045
That's child abuse.

07:34.587 --> 07:36.714
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

07:36.923 --> 07:38.413
What if there's an emergency...

07:38.591 --> 07:40.752
...and we don't have TV
to tell us what to do?

07:40.927 --> 07:42.189
Yeah. It's a safety issue.

07:42.361 --> 07:43.851
What is wrong with my children?

07:44.030 --> 07:46.294
You're acting
like this is the end of the world.

07:46.499 --> 07:49.059
How is it not? Tell me how it's not.

07:49.268 --> 07:51.759
Sorry, guys, but cable's gotta go.

07:51.938 --> 07:54.429
And you know what?
This just might be a good thing.

07:54.640 --> 07:58.303
Because maybe you'll start developing
interests beyond vegging on the couch.

07:59.045 --> 08:01.878
<i>MAN [ON TV]: Thirty-second warning.
- Yay! The check cleared.</i>

08:02.081 --> 08:03.105
KIDS [IN UNISON]:
TV!

08:03.282 --> 08:06.251
<i>SUE: Ha-ha-ha.
MAN: Listen, as some of our...</i>

08:06.786 --> 08:08.777
<i>FRANKIE:
The next day wasn't any easier for Brick.</i>

08:08.955 --> 08:10.547
BOY:
Bombs away.

08:10.756 --> 08:11.882
GIRL:
You leave him alone.

08:12.058 --> 08:13.548
I miss the library.

08:13.759 --> 08:14.783
[MEOWS]

08:15.027 --> 08:16.790
There's a bell here. It's gonna ring.

08:16.963 --> 08:19.591
It's gonna be too loud.
I gotta talk to Mr. Seifried.

08:19.765 --> 08:22.632
- You'll never make it.
ERIC: I gotta try.

08:24.070 --> 08:25.094
He's been hit.

08:25.538 --> 08:27.836
It's okay. He's fine.

08:28.040 --> 08:30.235
Nothing to see.

08:30.977 --> 08:33.639
Come on,
let's get you back into the library.

08:33.813 --> 08:36.280
I'm going home?

08:39.284 --> 08:43.619
Wait, Mr. Seifried.
We're not cut out for the playground.

08:43.823 --> 08:45.017
Zack's an indoor cat...

08:45.191 --> 08:48.319
...and Corey really needs to keep
his socks white or he'll freak.

08:48.494 --> 08:50.985
Come on, recess is good for you.

08:51.163 --> 08:53.188
Next week,
we're introducing dodge ball.

08:56.569 --> 08:59.163
<i>FRANKIE: So we didn't have cable.
Not the end of the world.</i>

08:59.338 --> 09:02.171
<i>We just went old school
and broke out the rabbit ears.</i>

09:03.009 --> 09:06.137
<i>Yeah, that whole digital-revolution thing
screwed us pretty good.</i>

09:06.312 --> 09:09.804
<i>But funny thing, the kids were handling
no TV better than expected.</i>

09:10.016 --> 09:14.953
<i>Sue was babysitting to raise money
for her future modeling career.</i>

09:16.088 --> 09:17.817
<i>Brick? Well, Brick read.</i>

09:17.990 --> 09:19.890
<i>Big surprise.</i>

09:20.126 --> 09:22.287
<i>Axl finally had time to start a band.</i>

09:22.461 --> 09:23.485
Let's rock.

09:23.663 --> 09:25.790
- Two, three, four.
- Wait.

09:26.399 --> 09:29.857
Who's rocking?
We don't have a name yet.

09:30.102 --> 09:31.729
Axl and the Axmen.

09:31.904 --> 09:33.201
- Two, three, four...
- Whoa, whoa.

09:33.739 --> 09:36.230
How come you're the one
to get your name in the name?

09:36.475 --> 09:39.876
Because your garage is filled
with your sister's gymnastics equipment.

09:40.046 --> 09:43.538
<i>FRANKIE: But the band never played.
And Mike and I?</i>

09:44.817 --> 09:46.307
Got any twos?

09:46.485 --> 09:48.749
Any twos?

09:49.188 --> 09:50.212
Go fish.

09:50.389 --> 09:51.515
[FRANKIE SIGHS]

09:52.491 --> 09:53.924
<i>FRANKIE:
Sue modeled.</i>

09:54.126 --> 09:55.150
[YELPS]

09:55.328 --> 09:57.558
<i>FRANKIE:
Brick read.</i>

09:58.264 --> 10:00.630
<i>Axl practiced.</i>

10:02.668 --> 10:05.000
<i>And Mike and I...</i>

10:06.772 --> 10:09.206
- This is nice.
- Yeah.

10:16.349 --> 10:17.373
[FRANKIE SIGHS]

10:17.550 --> 10:19.916
- We gotta get a hobby.
- Yeah.

10:24.423 --> 10:25.447
We're pathetic.

10:25.625 --> 10:28.924
How come our kids can think of things
to do besides TV and we can't?

10:29.095 --> 10:31.791
They're young.
They still find life interesting.

10:31.964 --> 10:33.158
Come on, we can do this.

10:33.332 --> 10:36.267
All right, the category is hobbies.

10:36.435 --> 10:37.459
[FRANKIE SIGHS]

10:37.637 --> 10:39.195
Bowling?

10:39.405 --> 10:41.202
- Costs money.
- Scrapbooking.

10:41.440 --> 10:43.032
I'm a man.

10:44.010 --> 10:45.034
[PHONE RINGS]

10:45.211 --> 10:46.508
I'll get it.

10:46.679 --> 10:49.512
Dad, would you write me a note
to get me out of recess?

10:49.715 --> 10:52.206
Recess?
Why would I want you out of recess?

10:52.418 --> 10:54.477
I love recess. Recess is the best part.

10:54.687 --> 10:56.985
For the strong.

10:57.156 --> 10:59.522
Why do I even bother?

11:00.626 --> 11:02.856
Guess who has plans
for tomorrow night.

11:03.029 --> 11:06.157
Aunt Edie and Aunt Ginny
have invited us to bingo at the church.

11:06.365 --> 11:09.357
You know,
a few weeks ago, I would've laughed.

11:09.535 --> 11:11.628
- But I'm actually excited.
FRANKIE: Yeah.

11:11.837 --> 11:12.963
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

11:16.876 --> 11:18.707
B-13.

11:18.944 --> 11:22.505
And don't forget to stamp
the middle square.

11:22.682 --> 11:25.242
- It's a freebie.
MIKE: Mm.

11:25.451 --> 11:28.045
[WHISPERS]
And if you wanna smoke...

11:30.389 --> 11:31.686
[COUGHS]

11:31.857 --> 11:33.518
No one will know.

11:33.726 --> 11:36.251
Thanks for the tip.
And the burn in my pants.

11:36.462 --> 11:38.259
HAYVER:
N-34.

11:38.464 --> 11:40.591
Look around, Mike. This is our future.

11:40.833 --> 11:44.496
Actually, this is your future.
All the men smartened up and died.

11:44.670 --> 11:45.762
G-56.

11:46.005 --> 11:48.200
<i>Aunt Edie,
what am I missing on The Bachelor?</i>

11:48.407 --> 11:50.602
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Three words. Hot-tub fight.

11:50.843 --> 11:53.243
- No.
- O-72.

11:53.479 --> 11:55.037
- Tara's still in the running?
- Frankie.

11:55.214 --> 11:58.775
- He's so handsome and she's so skanky.
- Frankie. Bingo.

11:59.018 --> 12:00.451
- You won?
- No, you won.

12:00.619 --> 12:01.950
FRANKIE: Oh. Oh.
- We got a bingo.

12:02.121 --> 12:03.611
Let's collect that prize and go.

12:03.789 --> 12:06.383
I hope it's the his and her
medic-alert bracelets.

12:06.592 --> 12:09.060
Yeah, all the bacon we eat,
they'll come in handy.

12:10.096 --> 12:13.554
Well, you picked a good night
to come to church.

12:13.766 --> 12:15.256
[MIKE CHUCKLES]

12:15.434 --> 12:21.566
Ladies and ladies,
we have our thousand-dollar winner.

12:21.774 --> 12:23.105
[CROWD APPLAUDS AND CHEERS]

12:23.275 --> 12:25.368
- A thousand dollars?
- Wait.

12:25.544 --> 12:28.945
A real thousand dollars?
Not like church bucks or diner coupons?

12:31.150 --> 12:32.742
- Oh, my God.
MIKE: Ha-ha-ha.

12:32.918 --> 12:35.443
[FRANKIE SHRIEKS THEN LAUGHS]

12:39.792 --> 12:43.990
I'm holding more money
than I ever have in my whole life.

12:44.163 --> 12:45.596
Wanna roll around in it?

12:45.798 --> 12:48.096
There's only ten bills here.
We'd feel stupid.

12:48.267 --> 12:52.101
Oh, this is so great.

12:52.271 --> 12:54.967
Oh, there is so much
we can do with this.

12:56.675 --> 13:00.076
Like our financial advisor said,
finally pay down our credit cards.

13:00.246 --> 13:04.580
Yeah, it's great.
Paying that down will feel great.

13:04.784 --> 13:06.274
So great.

13:06.485 --> 13:12.822
To know we're doing the right thing,
that's gonna really feel great.

13:13.058 --> 13:17.188
I mean, winning the money at church
is obviously some kind of sign from God.

13:17.363 --> 13:21.163
Or was it a test from God?

13:21.333 --> 13:24.598
A test to see
if we would use it to enjoy life.

13:24.770 --> 13:26.931
Well, there's a lot of things
to spend it on...

13:27.106 --> 13:30.200
...if we weren't gonna pay
the debt down.

13:30.876 --> 13:33.470
But you're right.
We should be responsible.

13:33.646 --> 13:35.170
FRANKIE:
Definitely.

13:35.347 --> 13:36.712
Although...

13:36.882 --> 13:39.715
Shouldn't how we spend the money
be a family decision?

13:40.386 --> 13:42.684
Yes. A family decision.

13:42.855 --> 13:46.188
Kids, get in here.
We need to talk to you.

13:46.525 --> 13:48.459
Oh, no. Mom's dying.

13:48.661 --> 13:50.322
Sit down.

13:50.529 --> 13:51.826
Now here's the deal.

13:52.031 --> 13:55.364
Dad and I won a substantial
amount of money at church bingo.

13:55.601 --> 13:57.000
- All right.
- Awesome.

13:57.169 --> 13:58.659
You were playing bingo?

13:58.871 --> 14:01.806
And we thought it only fair
that you guys weigh in...

14:01.974 --> 14:05.671
...and tell us what you think
we should do with the money.

14:05.878 --> 14:09.314
- Ah! I can get modeling classes.
- Whoa, I need a new amp.

14:09.515 --> 14:11.847
I need 20 bucks to bribe
a playground monitor.

14:12.017 --> 14:14.315
- Or hire a bully.
- Look, hold on.

14:14.486 --> 14:17.478
We were thinking
more along the lines of something...

14:17.656 --> 14:19.385
...the whole family could enjoy.

14:19.558 --> 14:21.048
Dad's right.

14:21.227 --> 14:23.252
We need something
that will make us happy.

14:23.429 --> 14:25.659
But what could that be?

14:25.865 --> 14:26.923
- Amp.
- Twenty bucks.

14:27.166 --> 14:28.394
- Modeling.
AXL: Sue, get real.

14:28.567 --> 14:30.899
Look at a supermodel
and then look at you.

14:31.070 --> 14:33.630
Oh, I could so be a supermodel.

14:33.839 --> 14:34.999
Mom. Dad.

14:35.174 --> 14:36.732
Couldn't I be a supermodel?

14:36.942 --> 14:38.409
FRANKIE: Yes.
- No.

14:39.044 --> 14:42.013
Well, like you could be a rock star.

14:42.214 --> 14:43.875
I just wanna get out of dodge ball.

14:44.083 --> 14:46.847
Look, I think we're getting away
from the point here.

14:47.052 --> 14:49.748
The point is we need to channel
all those thoughts...

14:49.922 --> 14:55.383
...and get a clear picture
of what would make us all happy.

14:55.594 --> 14:57.027
We told you what we wanted.

14:57.229 --> 14:58.753
You know what? You're all useless.

14:58.931 --> 15:00.398
This is an adult decision, get out.

15:00.566 --> 15:01.624
[AXL GROANS]

15:01.800 --> 15:03.097
[SUE SIGHS]

15:04.036 --> 15:05.060
[FRANKIE SIGHS]

15:05.237 --> 15:09.196
What the hell did we do right
that not a single one of them picked TV?

15:12.244 --> 15:13.575
<i>FRANKIE:
So we thought about it...</i>

15:13.746 --> 15:15.976
<i>...and in the light of day,
things seemed clearer.</i>

15:16.148 --> 15:20.585
The first thing we should do is not leave
a thousand dollars sitting on the counter.

15:20.753 --> 15:23.779
- Kids blew their shot. It's all here.
- Mm.

15:24.323 --> 15:27.690
I hate to say it, Mike,
but given our situation...

15:27.860 --> 15:29.987
...I think we both know
what we have to do.

15:30.162 --> 15:33.427
- Yep.
- Mom? Dad?

15:33.599 --> 15:34.930
If things go south today...

15:35.100 --> 15:37.967
...my personal effects
are in the peanut can under my bed.

15:38.170 --> 15:41.071
Good to know, son.
But you're not getting out of recess.

15:46.178 --> 15:48.112
I've been reconning all week...

15:48.314 --> 15:50.805
...and I have a plan
to get us back into the library.

15:50.983 --> 15:54.180
We just need to get Mr. Seifried
away from that door.

15:54.420 --> 15:57.446
Uh-uh. I'm too scared.
What if we get hit?

15:57.656 --> 16:00.784
Do you wanna stay
in this stinking playground forever?

16:00.993 --> 16:02.961
- No.
- All right, then.

16:03.762 --> 16:08.461
Now, my intel says the handball boys
hate the four-square boys.

16:08.667 --> 16:11.158
If we get them together,
it'll create a diversion...

16:11.337 --> 16:13.669
...giving us time
to make it to the library.

16:13.872 --> 16:16.170
- But how?
- With this.

16:16.342 --> 16:18.674
The key to the whole operation.

16:18.877 --> 16:21.107
The double-Dutch girls.

16:21.280 --> 16:22.440
[WHISPERS]
Double-Dutch.

16:23.382 --> 16:25.077
<i>BRICK [IN NORMAL VOICE]:
Here's the plan.</i>

16:25.284 --> 16:28.344
<i>We'll tell Rayna that one
of the four-square boys likes her.</i>

16:28.520 --> 16:30.147
Really?

16:31.123 --> 16:34.286
<i>BRICK: She'll run over to the four-square
boys to find out if it's true.</i>

16:34.460 --> 16:36.951
Hey, Mitch. I hear you like me.

16:37.162 --> 16:40.188
<i>BRICK: This will cause him to freak out
and drop the four-square ball.</i>

16:40.399 --> 16:41.832
<i>We'll grab it and throw it...</i>

16:42.001 --> 16:44.902
<i>...into the middle of the handball area,
wrecking their game.</i>

16:45.104 --> 16:46.901
Hey, your stupid ball messed us up.

16:47.139 --> 16:49.903
<i>BRICK: They'll blame the four-square
boys for ruining their game.</i>

16:50.109 --> 16:54.842
<i>And this will create a diversion,
causing Mr. Seifried to leave the door.</i>

16:55.614 --> 16:59.015
He's not moving. It's not working.

16:59.184 --> 17:00.811
Not yet.

17:05.723 --> 17:07.851
[KIDS SHRIEKING]

17:08.060 --> 17:09.686
BOY:
Candy!

17:09.862 --> 17:11.021
[WHISTLE TWEETS]

17:14.700 --> 17:15.723
Let's go.

17:18.237 --> 17:19.261
[WHISTLE TWEETING]

17:19.438 --> 17:20.734
Okay. All right.

17:20.906 --> 17:23.339
Don't eat, don't eat.
Everybody's friends.

17:23.541 --> 17:25.406
[WHISTLE TWEETING]

17:26.779 --> 17:28.679
COREY:
Oh, no.

17:28.881 --> 17:30.041
Leave me here, Brick.

17:30.215 --> 17:33.116
- Save yourself.
- No man left behind.

17:33.285 --> 17:35.219
- Come on.
COREY: I can't.

17:35.421 --> 17:38.390
My sock is so white.
I can't get it dirty.

17:46.965 --> 17:48.956
You saved my life.

17:49.168 --> 17:50.965
And my sock.

17:51.170 --> 17:55.038
<i>Semper fi, my brother. Semper fi.</i>

17:58.577 --> 18:00.568
<i>MAN [ON TV]:
Ha-ha-ha. I got you, no worries.</i>

18:00.779 --> 18:01.803
Oh.

18:01.980 --> 18:03.971
See,
you could've had the hot karate guy...

18:04.216 --> 18:06.650
...but you thought you could do better
and now you're stuck.

18:06.819 --> 18:07.877
[MAN LAUGHS ON TV]

18:08.053 --> 18:10.544
- How are you watching TV?
- I paid for the cable.

18:10.756 --> 18:14.157
I even prepaid for the whole year,
saved us 15 bucks.

18:14.326 --> 18:17.261
How's that
for smart financial planning? Hmm?

18:17.763 --> 18:18.991
Why did you do that?

18:19.698 --> 18:22.132
Because that's what we agreed on.
Come, sit.

18:22.301 --> 18:25.600
Watch. She passed on karate guy.

18:26.004 --> 18:29.235
Frankie, I wanted TV too
but we agreed to pay off the credit card.

18:29.408 --> 18:31.069
That's why I sent in a check.

18:31.243 --> 18:32.801
A check that's now gonna bounce.

18:33.479 --> 18:35.640
<i>- What? Wait.
MAN: And I also read palms. Could I...</i>

18:37.282 --> 18:40.410
Where did you get the idea
we agreed to pay off the credit card?

18:40.586 --> 18:43.214
This morning when you said,
"Given our situation..."

18:43.422 --> 18:47.017
Yeah, given our situation
that it sucks to not have any TV. Duh.

18:47.259 --> 18:51.218
I mean, we have no mind connection.
We'd be terrible on a game show.

18:51.964 --> 18:54.865
How in the world do you justify
spending the money on cable?

18:55.100 --> 18:57.762
Because I thought
we agreed to spin the wheel.

18:57.936 --> 19:01.463
You know, go for what we want
and take the risk that it'll all work out.

19:01.640 --> 19:04.165
- I thought we were both spinners.
- Oh, that's just great.

19:04.343 --> 19:06.811
Sue's gonna be a model,
Axl's gonna be a rock star.

19:06.979 --> 19:08.810
Some miracle will fall into our lap...

19:08.981 --> 19:11.779
...solve all our financial problems,
so let's just get TV.

19:11.950 --> 19:14.646
- You're delusional.
- Well, you're un-American.

19:14.853 --> 19:16.320
- What?
- That's right.

19:16.488 --> 19:19.457
Because real Americans are raised
on instant gratification...

19:19.658 --> 19:23.287
...and the optimism that if they mess up,
things will somehow all work out.

19:23.462 --> 19:25.828
That's what makes America great.

19:26.031 --> 19:27.658
How sad to be you.

19:27.866 --> 19:30.994
In your dark, little no-TV world.

19:31.170 --> 19:34.469
You're crazy if you think
something's just gonna drop in your lap.

19:34.640 --> 19:37.666
We just won $1000. How much
luck do you think we're entitled to?

19:37.843 --> 19:39.902
- Uh, Dad?
- All of it. All of it, Mike.

19:40.145 --> 19:41.476
I'm going for more.

19:41.680 --> 19:43.648
Big spin. Big spin.

19:43.815 --> 19:44.907
I'm going all the way.

19:45.150 --> 19:46.811
<i>FRANKIE:
Turns out the kids weren't wrong.</i>

19:46.985 --> 19:49.545
<i>A lot of important messages
do come over the TV.</i>

19:49.788 --> 19:53.417
Mom, Dad. The quarry's open.

19:56.828 --> 19:58.318
Wow.

19:58.497 --> 19:59.828
I'm going back to work.

20:00.032 --> 20:01.329
We won!

20:01.500 --> 20:04.492
Big winners! Big winners!

20:05.571 --> 20:07.038
What's going on?

20:07.239 --> 20:10.231
- I just got my job back.
- We spun and we won.

20:10.442 --> 20:11.739
[SHRIEKS]

20:12.377 --> 20:14.709
[BOTH SHRIEK]

20:14.880 --> 20:17.212
<i>FRANKIE:
See? It's not delusional.</i>

20:17.382 --> 20:21.910
<i>In a country where this is possible,
Sue could be a supermodel.</i>

20:22.955 --> 20:25.719
<i>Axl could be a rock star.</i>

20:26.758 --> 20:29.818
<i>Brick could be a great leader of men.</i>

20:31.396 --> 20:36.891
<i>You just gotta believe and keep spinning,
because you never know.</i>

20:42.741 --> 20:44.732
[ENGLISH - US - SDH]
